songs.title: Cartoons

description.plain:
A single from CupcakKe’s fifth project. This single was preceded by the single “Exit”, which was the lead single off CupcakKe’s fifth project.

Announced on 11/6/17 on CupcakKe’s social media, Cartoons is a call-back to earlier drill-songs from her first two mixtapes; “Cum Cake” & “S.T.D (Shelters to Deltas)”, which were mostly absent from her two studio albums “Audacious” & “Queen Elizabitch”, which both held a more ‘pop’ feel to it. While the themes are the same as some songs from the two albums, the delivery is very different then what we’ve seen recently.

The chorus (and a line from the first verse) reference multiple cartoon characters, which leads to the song’s name “Cartoons”. The cover shows a cartoon version of CupcakKe sporting a neon pink wig and pink clothes inside a TV, with multiple gloved hands (most notoriously seen on cartoon characters like Mickey Mouse and game characters like Cuphead) clawing up towards her. The background is just a normal yellow cover, except for rainbow text.

This song chocks in at 2:31, along with the prior single “Exit” clocking in at 2:47. Both of these songs are smaller then what is normally seen on her albums, and seem to call back to shorter tracks from her mixtapes. However, the content of both these songs show a mix of her older work and her newer work, with “Exit” being more pop-sided, with “Cartoons” being a traditional drill-styled song.

A great preview into what’s gonna come from CupcakKe in the coming months!

songs.title: Discounts

description.plain:
“Discounts” is CupcakKe’s 3rd single of 2020, following the release of “Lemon Pepper” and “Lawd Jesus” earlier in the year.

On June 18th, 2020, she announced the song would be released on June 26th, 2020. Five days later, as a teaser for its release, she posted a short snippet of the song on social media.

Shortly after its release, “Discounts” began rising on the iTunes charts, eventually reaching #1, becoming CupcakKe’s first #1 on iTunes. “Discounts” also became her first #1 in all genres on iTunes US, making her the first independent black female rapper to do this. After this, she revealed that 5 labels reached out to her.

Due to the single’s success on the iTunes charts, CupcakKe released a clean version of the song on June 29th, 2020.

songs.title: Exit

description.plain:
“Exit” is the lead single of the follow-up album to “Queen Elizabitch”, which received positive reviews from music publications like Pitchfork

Lyrically, it’s about CupcakKe frustrated at his ex to the point where she demands him to “exit” out of her life.

This song continues the bubbly and fun rap that we’ve seen very apparent in Queen Elizabitch. However, while Queen Elizabitch did have a lot of darker themes mixed in with the pop-inspired tracks, Exit seems to follow with these tones.

This song was released to acclaim by fans, immediately becoming her 3rd most popular song on Spotify after less then a week of release.

While this song is still very popular, CupcakKe followed up this track with her second single from her next album, which was titled “Cartoons”, which has since pushed Exit down lower to the popular list, and is all that fans can talk about!

As has been seen with nearly every one of CupcakKe’s lead singles, once the album is released, they usually end up being average compared to other tracks; Good examples of this are “Picking Cotton”, the lead single from “Audacious”, and “Cumshot”, the lead single from “Queen Elizabitch”

This, however, is good for all of CupcakKe’s slurpers, as this means that her third studio album (5th project in total) is going to be absolutely amazing!
